source.name: Transaction Costs - OECD Economic Outlook (2007)
source.dataPublishedBy: OECD Insights - Economic Globalisation: Origins and Consequences
source.dataPublisherSource: OECD (2007), OECD Economic Outlook, Vol. 2007/1, OECD Publishing.
source.additionalInfo: Sea fright corresponds to average international freight charges per tonne. Passenger air transport corresponds to average airline revenue per passenger mile until 2000 spliced to US import air passenger fares afterwards. International calls correspond to cost of a three-minute call from New York to London.
